The error message contains this hint 

&gt; Cannot deserialize object in variable

If you need to serialize/deserialize a class, this class has to implement the interface `java.io.Serializable`. And any class used for fields in that class have toimplement the interface `Serializable` also. 

As shown in the question, your class `MyObject` does not implement the interface `Serializable`

    public class MyObject {

Now looking at the fields of `MyObject`

    private String name;

`String` implements `Serializable` therefore `String` ist serializable.

    public final class String
        implements java.io.Serializable, Comparable&lt;String&gt;, CharSequence {

    private List&lt;String&gt; values;

As interface `List` and its inherited interfaces do not implement the interface `Serializable` it depends on the used implementation of `List` if it is serializable. `ArrayList` for example is serializable.

    public interface List&lt;E&gt; extends Collection&lt;E&gt; {
    public interface Collection&lt;E&gt; extends Iterable&lt;E&gt; {
    public interface Iterable&lt;T&gt; {

    public class ArrayList&lt;E&gt; extends AbstractList&lt;E&gt;
        implements List&lt;E&gt;, RandomAccess, Cloneable, java.io.Serializable

As conclusion you have to add the interface `Serializable`

   public class MyObject implements Serializable

and you have to use a serializable implementation of `List`.

To learn more about serialization at [Oracle guide serialization][1]


  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/technotes/guides/serialization/index.html

